Running Basex with docker compose

1. Some folders and files from the basex root folder, are required to run the docker-compose file:

	1. data containing database files 
	2. webapp containing clarin and WEB-INF
	3. .basex configuration file
	4. .env file containing environment variables	

2. Set enviroment variables in the .env file

	Set the paths to data, webapp and basex conf files. 
	Set up gid and uid by checking id
	
	$id

3. running basex

	$docker compose up

	-d detached


4. Update/replace database

	$ docker compose exec sis-bx sh

	~/basex $ ./bin/basex
	
	> create backup data
	> create db data /opt/basex/webapp/clarin/data